1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,400
Can we listen to Rivat Gabai?
-Can we listen to Justin Bieber?

2
00:00:03,520 --> 00:00:05,480
No, no, no, no Justin and no Rivat Gabai.

3
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:08,680
Enough already, today we’re listening to
what Mom and Dad want, enough.

4
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:13,280
Well, Per Olsson, the Swedish hit
that’s topping the charts worldwide

5
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:14,880
is visiting the country.

6
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:17,080
Tonight at the cultural hall.

7
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,440
Hey, why don’t we go
to a show at the cultural hall sometime?

8
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:20,800
He’s Swedish.

9
00:00:21,320 --> 00:00:23,880
Do you know any of his songs?
-No, I wasn’t talking about his specific show,

10
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:25,840
any show, play, movie,

11
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:28,720
concert, melodrama, exhibit, something.

12
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:36,720
What’s that?

13
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:38,680
World music.

14
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,000
What a disaster, what is this?

15
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:42,680
Besides the song being bad and boring
the lyrics, what are those lyrics?

16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,120
What, is it in German?

17
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,200
No, it’s Swedish,
it sounds like German but softer.

18
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:53,400
In German, if you want to say
"I love you,"

19
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:57,120
you say "Ich liebe dich."

20
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,160
It’s sharp, rough.

21
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:02,960
And in Swedish, you say

22
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,640
Jag älskar dig.
-Oh, really?

23
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:07,000
Like a sputtering Volvo.

24
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,000
I think about those Swedes,

25
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:11,720
what have they brought to the world
besides Volvo and ABBA?

26
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:12,760
What else do they have to offer?

27
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:15,520
True.

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,200
Tell me, how do you know how to say
"I love you" in Swedish?

29
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:22,440
What?

30
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:26,080
Change the subject, please.

31
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:35,440
Look at me, look at me and...

32
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,680
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

33
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,200
Shabbat Shalom, Dad.

34
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,800
Did something happen?
-No, no, everything’s great.

35
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,400
Great?

36
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,840
What did you do to her?
-Nothing.

37
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,080
Got it.

38
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:02,080
I just told her in the car
about a tiny romance I had once

39
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,360
and she got all upset.

40
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:05,920
Big mistake.

41
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:09,280
You made the mistake they teach in lesson one

42
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,800
at the school for beginner husbands

43
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:14,920
"Introduction to the Hurt Woman."

44
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,240
What’s the lesson?

45
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:19,200
Shut your mouth.

46
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,120
You understand?

47
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:28,040
Never tell her anything
about your past relationships

48
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,000
because they get really hurt by that.

49
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,120
But how can they be hurt if it was before
I even met her, before the army?

50
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,400
No, no, you don’t understand, you don’t get it.

51
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:39,080
Women don’t have timelines, past, present, future.
You understand?

52
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:44,440
Women have spatial time, for them everything is present.

53
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,720
Got it.
-Yeah.

54
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:50,920
So what do I do now?
-Nothing, move on to chapter two,

55
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,920
the apology.

56
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,680
Honey, what happened?
-Nothing, nothing.

57
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:00,040
What did Shai do?
-Just put me in some bad movie.

58
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,800
What movie?
-Turns out he had a fling with a Swedish girl at some kibbutz.

59
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:06,080
Which kibbutz?
-Beit Zera, I know which kibbutz.

60
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:09,800
Turns out he volunteered there
picking avocados before the army.

61
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,560
Son, that was before he met her.

62
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,520
Boy
Oh boy.

63
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,680
So why didn't he tell me?
-Did you ask him?

64
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,640
No, but still, she's Swedish, right?

65
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:20,240
Come on, sweetie, don’t think about it,
it just gives you heartache.

66
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:21,600
Forget it, it’ll be forgotten.

67
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:24,720
Okay, but why did he hide it from me
all these years? I don’t get it.

68
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,960
Shani, I couldn’t help but listen to the conversation.

69
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,000
I totally get you.

70
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:32,920
It’s just infuriating, and let me tell you,
from my messed-up experience with guys,

71
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:36,400
a guy who hides a little, hides a lot.

72
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:41,120
Come on, really, Shai, he’s such a good boy.

73
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:44,800
A good boy should have told everything
on the first or second date,

74
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,560
and preferably the first because there’s no second chance.

75
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,120
Okay, enough, Meirav, you’re exaggerating.

76
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,920
Shani, can I talk to you for a sec?
-Yeah, sure, no problem.

77
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:56,680
Just how do you say "please" in Swedish?
-Uh..

78
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:03,560
I don’t get the excitement
Israelis have for Scandinavians,

79
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,920
most of them, by the way, are big girls who don’t shave,

80
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,440
hairy for the sake of Helga, with blonde braids

81
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:09,960
and cowbells around their necks.

82
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,160
Honey, ask any guy in the world,

83
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:18,839
they’ll all tell you there’s nothing like Israeli girls.
-True.

84
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,560
Okay, I get that I need to apologize.
-Of course.

85
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:29,040
Look, this was before I enlisted
at some avocado farm up north.

86
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:32,240
I was dead, exhausted,

87
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:36,960
because the avocados there were huge,
big and heavy too,

88
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,080
and the guys had a few drinks.

89
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,480
A few volunteers showed up, that’s all.

90
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,120
What did I do wrong?

91
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,200
I just thought we had no secrets between us.

92
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,640
Shani, it’s not secrets, it’s history, okay?

93
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,720
It’s prehistory.

94
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:53,840
Fine, that’s your past, and now
you live in our shared present, right?

95
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,160
Shani.
-No, don’t call me Shani.

96
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:57,520
If you disconnect your past from our present,

97
00:04:57,760 --> 00:05:00,440
then we won’t have a shared future together.
-Okay, okay.

98
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:04,640
I made a mistake not telling you.
-True.

99
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,000
Sorry.

100
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:08,960
It’s fine.

101
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,840
So how was she?
-Why? Why?

102
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,840
No, I want to know.

103
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,840
If I tell you, we won’t talk about it anymore?
-Yeah, go on, how was she?

104
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,680
I know, Swedish.

105
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,760
Blonde?
-Swedish.

106
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,440
What, tall, short, fat, skinny, big chest?

107
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,360
I don’t know? Like an avocado.

108
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:30,400
You said we wouldn’t talk about it anymore.
-You said that.

109
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,600
Go on?
-I apologized like a champ.

110
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:40,520
Fine.
-A ton of apologies and bowing down to the ground.

111
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,000
Not in the mood.
-Oh, not in the mood?

112
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:50,680
Tell me, did she ask you how the other one looked?
-Right.

113
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:51,840
Yeah
you, son
boy.

114
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,880
And you idiot, you probably told her the truth.
-Oh no.

115
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,680
Do I need to apologize again?
-No, no, you can’t apologize,

116
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:04,400
there’s no point in apologizing, it’s all lost now,
it’s complicated now,

117
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,880
it’s already a level three language course.

118
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,960
Who’s calling on a Friday?

119
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,440
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

120
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:19,240
This is Silvan Hasson’s apartment.
-Yes, Silvan Hasson, that’s me.

121
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:23,160
Big problem, I'm Dana,
can I talk to you for a sec in private?

122
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,640
What do you mean in private?
-No, it's fine, I have nothing to hide.

123
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,600
Please, have a seat.
-Thanks.

124
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,000
I'm again
in a big problem, and...

125
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,760
Dana.
-Sit down.

126
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:41,320
So my name is Dana and I'm the producer of a documentary

127
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:44,560
about the famous Swedish singer Per Olsson, you know him?

128
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:46,480
Hello, hello, nothing more than that.

129
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,640
Really?
-No.

130
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:53,640
But on the way here we heard in the car
by chance a rap song by that singer.

131
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,960
How is all this related to us?

132
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:59,080
So here's the thing, they're making a film on Swedish TV about Per,

133
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,680
Moshe! Like the master! Like that,

134
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:03,720
and I'm the producer on the Israeli side.

135
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:07,280
The story actually started when he
came to the country to find his lost dad,

136
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,720
he grew up without a father.

137
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,920
And because he's very, very famous

138
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,640
they decided to document this search in a documentary.

139
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:17,560
Nice.
-No, still not clear why you're here.

140
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,600
Because according to the research they did back in Sweden,

141
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:25,400
they discovered that his dad met his mom here in the country

142
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:28,880
at Kibbutz Ein Hores in the summer of 1966.

143
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,200
Wow... 19... check this out,

144
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:36,880
1966 I was at Kibbutz Ein Ha...

145
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,640
Yeah, and you met volunteers from abroad there.

146
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:45,840
Sali, is... is this real what's happening here?

147
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,920
No, Racheli, I'm hearing about this for the first time.

148
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,880
Of course, of course it's not real, obviously,

149
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,960
she wasn't Swedish, she was Scandinavian.

150
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:58,080
Sweden is a Scandinavian country.
-Oh, really?

151
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,800
Rachel...
-I told you I prefer privacy.

152
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,040
Excuse me, okay?

153
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:11,120
I'm Shani, I'm their daughter,
can you please continue the story?

154
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,120
Yeah, to make it shorter
-to shorten, yeah.

155
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:18,200
What actually happened is that after their brief romance

156
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,400
she went back to Sweden,

157
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:25,560
and your dad didn't know he left her
a little gift from the Holy Land

158
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:30,880
that later became the singer Per Olsson
who is actually your half-brother.

159
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,080
Wow.

160
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,000
Tell me, is it okay to include you in the film?

161
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,000
Wow.

162
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:45,400
Racheli, come on, that was so long ago.

163
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,960
That was before we were together.

164
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:52,880
Before there was even a settlement law.
-I don't know, Sali, I don't know.

165
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:57,400
I was wrong, sorry, okay?

166
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,080
Okay.

167
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,200
What was she like?
-What do you mean what was she like? Come on, she was...

168
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:10,320
Short, she had this short hair,

169
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:16,240
with a blonde mustache, with stubble like that, come on.

170
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:18,440
Yeah, okay, okay, okay.

171
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:21,840
How was her voice?
-Her voice?

172
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,840
She didn't have a voice.

173
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:30,640
She spoke Swedish, I spoke
Hebrew, and we didn't even need to talk,

174
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,200
we just communicated with gestures.
-Oh, sure, with gestures,

175
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:36,400
who needs words when you have a talented choreographer like you-

176
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,040
Enough, Rach...
-Without words.

177
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:42,280
Listen, he came all the way to the country
for this, for the film,

178
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,240
he learned Hebrew.

179
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:47,200
If they refuse, it would be really nice
to at least talk to some of the family.

180
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,160
What, what are you saying?

181
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,960
Very problematic.

182
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:56,120
Maybe you should tell her that in Swedish too.
-Come on, babe, why...

183
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,000
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

184
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:03,680
Who do we have the honor of meeting?
-Hi, Dana, film producer.

185
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,000
They're filming a movie about the Hasson family living in a movie.

186
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,680
That's interesting,

187
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:13,600
She's here to film a movie about Silvan
meeting his long-lost son from Sweden.

188
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,800
-What son?

189
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:19,640
So it turns out your dad
once had a fling with a Swedish volunteer

190
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:22,080
and he didn't know he left her with a kid.

191
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,160
No way.
-Absolutely.

192
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,280
That guy grew up to be a famous singer in Sweden.

193
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:29,520
Per Olsson?
-I think you're the only one who knows him.

194
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,000
And what does Mom say about all this?
-She doesn't say much,

195
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,040
she's more at a loss for words.

196
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:36,000
Wait, she didn't get the last word?
-Shh...

197
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,160
What's with the shh and the silence?

198
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,080
Shabbat Shalom.

199
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,400
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Manny, Shabbat Shalom, Alin.

200
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:45,000
Sorry, I just want to know if everything's sorted out.

201
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,920
Can we start filming?
-No, absolutely not.

202
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,720
I thought you knew that book by heart.

203
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,800
I didn't know she knew it too, she...

204
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:57,840
She really surprised me.

205
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:02,040
Tell me, if they don't agree, would you
be willing to film with your half-brother?

206
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,400
You think?

207
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,480
Dad, tell me, is he older than me?

208
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:11,920
Mom, come on, maybe you should forgive Dad too?
-Why, because you forgave Shai?

209
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:15,200
It's not the same, Mom,
it's nonsense Dad did years ago.

210
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:18,080
Yeah, but from Dad's nonsense
a kid was born, and that's not funny anymore.

211
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,880
A kid? He's about to be a grandpa.

212
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:23,920
Let them film that
emotional scene, their reunion,

213
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:27,200
and they can take their awful songs
back to Sweden.

214
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,840
Shai, I know it's childish but...

215
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,960
I don't want them filming this movie here.

216
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,560
Mom, come on.

217
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:39,000
Tell me, didn't you have guys before Dad?

218
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,840
Me? No way.

219
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:45,440
Well, nothing serious.
-And does Dad know about it?

220
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,280
He knows most of it.

221
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:51,160
But not everything.
-Not everything, he doesn't need to know everything,

222
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,480
it's the first chapter in "How to Manage Men."

223
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:55,560
Of course, it's still in the introduction.

224
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,080
That comes later. I only had two guys before you.

225
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,600
And one of them was when I was drunk.
-Exactly.

226
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:05,160
Mr. Hasson, I'm begging you.
Your meeting with him is the whole movie.

227
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,560
If I don't have a meeting, I don't have a movie.

228
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:09,960
Listen carefully, I'm not willing to hurt
my wife's feelings.

229
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:15,200
If Rachel doesn't agree to the movie, there won't be a movie.

230
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,720
Tell me, even if he doesn't agree,

231
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,960
can we get a couple
of tickets to the show?

232
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,600
Shabbat Shalom.

233
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:25,120
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

234
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,280
Sorry for being late,
we just couldn't find the car keys.

235
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:31,560
Great, Moshe, you had an hour and a half drive.

236
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,480
Is that the excuse you came up with?

237
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,360
